</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> decided that the cost of rehousing would be greater than finding a way roun</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">d the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">social sector size criteria or ‘</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">bedroom tax</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; padding-bottom:1pt; padding-left:1pt; padding-right:1pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><div style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; clear:both; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; padding-bottom:10pt; padding-left:4pt; padding-right:4pt; padding-top:1pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">3. Our own experiences</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; padding-bottom:10pt; padding-left:4pt; padding-right:4pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">3.1 </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; padding-bottom:10pt; padding-left:4pt; padding-right:4pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Linkage Community Trust had one service user who moved into a 2-bedroom property in February 2013 as he required sleep-in staff due to his needs. The recent changes to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">housing benefits may have affected him but, due to staff incurring extra utility costs, Linkage only charged this service user the 1-bedro</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">om rent fee to compensate this.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; padding-bottom:10pt; padding-left:4pt; padding-right:4pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Although most of our service users live in 1-bedroom properties, we are anticipating t</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">hat those service users in 2-bed accommodation may be affected by the changes to housing-related benefits in the near future as they are re-assessed for housing benefits. This is because their current housing benefi</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ts applications are historical.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; padding-bottom:1pt; padding-left:4pt; padding-right:4pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">23 August 2013</span></p><div style="border-top-color:#d9d9d9; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; clear:both; margin:0pt"><p style="margin:0pt; padding-top:1pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>